==Russian==
===Etymology===
From [[–ľ—Ď–ī]] ([[honey]], [[mead]]) and [[-–Ķ–ī]] ([[eater]]), hence literally "''one who eats honey''". There is also a folk etymology from [[–ľ—Ď–ī]] and [[–≤–Ķ–ī–į—ā—Ć]] (to [[know]], to [[manage]]), hence "''one who knows honey''" or "''a master of honey''".

===Noun===
